      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASHANTE PRINCE (2) scored at the first run back from a break last time out over 1800m at this track on May 9, finishing 4 metres ahead of his rivals. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Must raise the bar but another win is not out of the question. HUGH GO (5) impressed when successful at this circuit two runs ago then settled back and failed to finish off well enough at his latest appearance over 1800m here, beaten 9 metres into fifth. Meeting a deeper field this time but he is up to the challenge. MANDS PEARL (3) disappointed last time when eighth over 1690m at Shepparton. Can bounce back from the favourable draw. PARISIAN BANDIT (1) is worth another chance after a last-start tenth over 1690m at Shepparton two weeks ago. Include from the pegs.",
